cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with using neural codes as visual descriptors for image retrieval, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of PCA compression and discriminative dimensionality reduction, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper mentions retraining the neural network on a dataset, which is a common technique in neural network optimization (cs.NE).
